) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]

    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]

) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]

If 'SaveChanges' fails, then the transaction cannot be automatically rolled back to a known clean state. Instead, the transaction should be rolled back by the application before retrying 'SaveChanges'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2149338 for more information and examples. To identify the code which triggers this warning, call 'ConfigureWarnings(w => w.Throw(SqlServerEventId.SavepointsDisabledBecauseOfMARS))'.

    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]

    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]

) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]

    SELECT [u0].[UserId], [u0].[GroupId]
    FROM [UserGroups] AS [u0]
    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]

    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]

INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [u0].[UserId], [u0].[GroupId]
    FROM [UserGroups] AS [u0]
    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]
    FROM [GroupsMenus] AS [g1]
    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]

SELECT DISTINCT [g2].[Access], [g2].[CanDelete], [g2].[CanInsert], [g2].[CanUpdate], [m0].[IconClass], [g2].[MenuID] AS [MenuId], [m0].[Name], [m0].[Path], [m0].[ParentID] AS [MenuParentId], [u].[Username]
FROM [Users] AS [u]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [u0].[UserId], [u0].[GroupId]
    FROM [UserGroups] AS [u0]
    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]
    FROM [GroupsMenus] AS [g1]
    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]
WHERE [u].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [m0].[Path] IS NOT NULL AND [m0].[Path] NOT LIKE N'' AND LOWER([m0].[Path]) = @__ToLower_0

) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]

    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]

) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]

SELECT DISTINCT [g2].[Access], [g2].[CanDelete], [g2].[CanInsert], [g2].[CanUpdate], [m0].[IconClass], [g2].[MenuID] AS [MenuId], [m0].[Name], [m0].[Path], [m0].[ParentID] AS [MenuParentId], [u].[Username]
FROM [Users] AS [u]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [u0].[UserId], [u0].[GroupId]
    FROM [UserGroups] AS [u0]
    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]
    FROM [GroupsMenus] AS [g1]
    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]
WHERE [u].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [m0].[Path] IS NOT NULL AND [m0].[Path] NOT LIKE N'' AND LOWER([m0].[Path]) = @__ToLower_0

SELECT DISTINCT [g2].[Access], [g2].[CanDelete], [g2].[CanInsert], [g2].[CanUpdate], [m0].[IconClass], [g2].[MenuID] AS [MenuId], [m0].[Name], [m0].[Path], [m0].[ParentID] AS [MenuParentId], [u].[Username]
FROM [Users] AS [u]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [u0].[UserId], [u0].[GroupId]
    FROM [UserGroups] AS [u0]
    WHERE [u0].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]
    FROM [GroupsMenus] AS [g1]
    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]
WHERE [u].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [m0].[Path] IS NOT NULL AND [m0].[Path] NOT LIKE N'' AND LOWER([m0].[Path]) = @__ToLower_0

If 'SaveChanges' fails, then the transaction cannot be automatically rolled back to a known clean state. Instead, the transaction should be rolled back by the application before retrying 'SaveChanges'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2149338 for more information and examples. ) AS [u1] ON [u].[id] = [u1].[UserId]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g].[id]
    FROM [Groups] AS [g]
    WHERE [g].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g0] ON [u1].[GroupId] = [g0].[id]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [g1].[GroupID], [g1].[MenuID], [g1].[Access], [g1].[CanDelete], [g1].[CanInsert], [g1].[CanUpdate]
    FROM [GroupsMenus] AS [g1]
    WHERE [g1].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [g2] ON [g0].[id] = [g2].[GroupID]
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT [m].[id], [m].[IconClass], [m].[Name], [m].[ParentID], [m].[Path]
    FROM [Menus] AS [m]
    WHERE [m].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit)
) AS [m0] ON [g2].[MenuID] = [m0].[id]
WHERE [u].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [m0].[Path] IS NOT NULL AND [m0].[Path] NOT LIKE N'' AND LOWER([m0].[Path]) = @__ToLower_0
2025-07-26 17:39:51.622 +03:00 [INF] Executed DbCommand (4ms) [Parameters=[], CommandType='"Text"', CommandTimeout='30']
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM [PersonsIDDetails] AS [p]
WHERE [p].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [p].[Persons_IDN] = 2

SELECT [p].[PersonsIDDetailIDN], [p].[IDExpiryActiveReminder], [p].[CreatedBy], [p].[CreationDate], [p].[IDExpiryDate], [p].[IDIssueDate], [p].[IDNumber], [p].[IsDeleted], [p].[IDPrimary], [p].[UpdatedBy], [p].[Modification_Date], [p].[IDNationality], [p].[PersonsIDDetailIDC], [p].[Persons_IDN], [p].[IDPlaceOfIssue], [p].[IDType]
FROM [PersonsIDDetails] AS [p]
WHERE [p].[IsDeleted] = CAST(0 AS bit) AND [p].[Persons_IDN] = 2
ORDER BY (SELECT 1)
OFFSET @__p_0 ROWS FETCH NEXT @__p_1 ROWS ONLY
